-- Standalone varied comments: helpful answers
(69, 1, 'For slow Postgres queries, start with EXPLAIN ANALYZE. Look for sequential scans on large tables first. Usually a missing index.', NOW() - INTERVAL '178 days 12 hours 30 minutes'),
(26, 5, 'Cache aside pattern works great for reads. For writes, prefer write-through if consistency matters more than latency.', NOW() - INTERVAL '169 days 0 hours 45 minutes'),
(51, 20, 'For JWTs, keep the access token short-lived (15 min) and use refresh tokens with rotation. Revoke the refresh token on logout.', NOW() - INTERVAL '161 days 7 hours 18 minutes'),
(87, 45, 'If you''re drowning in Docker networking issues, try running docker network inspect. 90% of the time it''s a subnet conflict.', NOW() - INTERVAL '147 days 14 hours 55 minutes'),
(60, 4, 'Set up alerts on your 99th percentile latency, not your average. Average hides the pain from your worst-off users.', NOW() - INTERVAL '139 days 2 hours 8 minutes'),
(94, 46, 'For DNS propagation issues, use dig +trace to see exactly where the resolution chain breaks. Saves hours of guessing.', NOW() - INTERVAL '131 days 18 hours 33 minutes'),
(45, 3, 'If your GitHub Actions are slow, cache your dependencies and use a matrix strategy for test parallelism. Cut our build time from 20min to 6.', NOW() - INTERVAL '123 days 11 hours 48 minutes'),
(75, 47, 'Try-catch everything at the boundary of your system (HTTP handlers, queue consumers). Let internal code throw. Log at the boundary with full context.', NOW() - INTERVAL '116 days 4 hours 5 minutes'),
(99, 69, 'Start a11y work with the low-hanging fruit: alt text on images, proper heading hierarchy, and keyboard focus management. Those three cover a huge percentage of issues.', NOW() - INTERVAL '108 days 16 hours 22 minutes'),
(38, 77, 'When dealing with cookies, always set SameSite=Lax at minimum. Strict is better if your users don''t follow links from external sites.', NOW() - INTERVAL '100 days 9 hours 38 minutes'),
(16, 54, 'For query optimization: check your indexes first, look at the execution plan, then consider if you even need that JOIN.', NOW() - INTERVAL '92 days 1 hour 52 minutes'),
(55, 72, 'Hot module replacement not working? Check that your component file has a default export. Vite needs it for the HMR boundary.', NOW() - INTERVAL '84 days 17 hours 10 minutes'),
(29, 86, 'For database backups: test your restores regularly. A backup you can''t restore from is not a backup.', NOW() - INTERVAL '76 days 8 hours 28 minutes'),

